See also: mude and mudé

German[edit]

Alternative forms[edit]

  • müd'
  • müd (colloquial or poetic)

Etymology[edit]

From Middle High German müede, muode, from Old High German muodi, from Proto-Germanic *mōþijaz, *mōþaz. Cognate to Dutch moe.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /ˈmyːdə/
  • audio (Germany)
    		(file)
  • audio (Austria)
    		(file)

Adjective[edit]

müde (comparative müder, superlative am müdesten)

  1. tired
